data-itemid="156293727" onclick="productdescpop(156293727)" class="desc SLC_wwbw SLC_pr SLC_brs1 SLC_cp filledDescHover">Magnetic Drive Pumps are a type of centrifugal pump that operates without a direct physical connection between the motor and the pump shaft. Instead, the pump uses a magnetic coupling to transfer energy from the motor to the pump impeller, offering significant benefits in terms of leakage prevention, maintenance, and safety. <span lis_catop"><h2 style="display:inline;margin-top: -3px;" onclick="opencatPopup(183082713);">Category</h2><span style="display:none;" title="Edit Category" onclick="opencatPopup(183082713)" class="categediticon icon-sprite"></span><div class="chipsL1 SLC_dflx SLC_dflw SLC_tac"><div class="chip1 SLC_f13 SLC_cp SLC_c0" title="Air Operated Pump" onclick="opencatPopup(183082713);">Air Operated Pump</div><div class="chip1 SLC_f13 SLC_cp SLC_c0" title="Double Diaphragm Pump" onclick="opencatPopup(183082713);">Double Diaphragm Pump</div><div class="chip1 SLC_f13 SLC_cp SLC_c0" title="Air Operated Diaphragm Pump" onclick="opencatPopup(183082713);">Air Operated Diaphragm Pump</div></div></div><div style="margin-top: 10px" class="SLC_pr SLC_w1"><h2 style="display:inline;" class="prdDescHeadCard" onclick="productdescpop(183082713)">Product Description</h2><span id="descidrbtn_183082713" data-itemid="183082713" onclick="productdescpop(183082713)" class="desc SLC_wwbw SLC_pr SLC_brs1 SLC_cp filledDescHover">We are offering&nbsp;Air Operated Double Diaphragm Pump.Other Details: An AODD pump is a type of positive displacement pump that uses compressed air as a power source.
The compressed air is shifted from one chamber to the other by a linked shaft that allows the chambers to move simultaneously.
This back-and-forth motion forces liquid out of one chamber and into the discharge piping while the other chamber is being filled with liquid at the same time.
These pumps use reciprocating elastomeric diaphragms and check valves to pump fluid.
The liquid chambers are filled and emptied by fluid that is drawn through a common inlet and discharged through a single outlet. Special Features: No electrical motor - non sparking.
No mechanical seals or gland packing.
The pumps can run dry indefinitely without damage.
Safe for use in hazardous / explosive environments.
Variable flow - simply regulate the inlet air supply to adjust the pump flow from zero to max.
If discharge is clogged or closed pump stops i <span class="SLC_imgc SLC_c1 SLC_f16 SLC_fwb SLC_gap5 SLC_cp filledDescHover"></span></span><div id="desceditarea_183082713" data-itemid="183082713" data-itemid="135736347" onclick="productdescpop(135736347)" class="desc SLC_wwbw SLC_pr SLC_brs1 SLC_cp filledDescHover">We are offering Horizontal Multistage Centrifugal Water Pump.Other Details: Characterised by a sturdy and compact construction. Available in various versions and models and suitable for many applications: pressure groups, water distribution and treatment, heating and air conditioning, cooling and chiller, irrigation and rainwater recovery, industrial washing and industrial systems.
Body, impellers, intermediate stages, seal holder disc and shaft (part in contact with the liquid) in AISI 304.
The standard mechanical seal is in Ceramic/Carbon/EPDM; then there is the possibility of using different types of special seals to reach a temperature range from -15°C to +110°C.
WRAS-certified for standard models up to 85°C.
It is possible to combine these pumps with 2 poles, self-ventilated, high efficiency asynchronous motors. Technical Data: IE3 high efficiency motors starting from 0.75 kW

They are constructed with semi-open impellers. They are manufactured by very specialized lost wax process for having minimum rejections with castings, having better impeller profiles in the castings resulting in optimum flow and efficiencies and delivering pumps at a speedy rate.Advantages of semi-open impellers: Can handle Slurries and solids content upto 30-40%.
All the impellers have back vanes which helps in reducing the radial and Axial Thrust on the Bearings.
With smooth flow passages and larger eye area it helps in easy flow of slurries and solids content.
Higher efficient even with slurries. Applications of Pumps: Distilleries(Fermentation and Evaporation Section)

class="SLC_pr SLC_w1"><h2 style="display:inline;" class="prdDescHeadCard" onclick="productdescpop(288870598)">Product Description</h2><span id="descidrbtn_288870598" data-itemid="288870598" onclick="productdescpop(288870598)" class="desc SLC_wwbw SLC_pr SLC_brs1 SLC_cp filledDescHover">An End Suction Pump is a type of centrifugal pump where the liquid enters the pump from one end (the suction side) and exits from the top or the discharge side of the pump casing. This design is one of the most common and widely used types of pumps in various industries, especially for handling clean or mildly contaminated fluids. These pumps are typically used for water transfer, HVAC systems, irrigation, and other industrial applications. <span class="SLC_imgc SLC_c1 SLC_f16 SLC_fwb SLC_gap5 SLC_cp that uses non-metallic materials for the construction of key components, such as the casing, impeller, and wear rings, instead of metals like stainless steel or cast iron. These pumps are designed to handle fluids that are corrosive, abrasive, or otherwise harmful to metals, making them ideal for specific applications in industries like chemicals, food processing, onclick="opencatPopup(135738321);">Pneumatic Diaphragm Pump</div><div class="chip1 SLC_f13 SLC_cp SLC_c0" title="ARO Diaphragm Pumps" onclick="opencatPopup(135738321);">ARO Diaphragm Pumps</div></div></div><div style="margin-top: 10px" class="SLC_pr SLC_w1"><h2 style="display:inline;" class="prdDescHeadCard" onclick="productdescpop(135738321)">Product Description</h2><span id="descidrbtn_135738321" data-itemid="135738321" onclick="productdescpop(135738321)" class="desc SLC_wwbw SLC_pr SLC_brs1 SLC_cp filledDescHover">We are offering Air Operated Double Diaphragm Pump.Other Details: An AODD pump is a type of positive displacement pump that uses compressed air as a power source. The compressed air is shifted from one chamber to the other by a linked shaft that allows the chambers to move simultaneously. This back-and-forth motion forces liquid out of one chamber and into the discharge piping while the other chamber is being filled with liquid at the same time. These pumps use reciprocating elastomeric diaphragms and check valves to pump fluid. The liquid chambers are filled and emptied by fluid that is drawn through a common inlet and discharged through a single outlet. Special Features: No electrical motor - non sparking.
No mechanical seals or gland packing.
The pumps can run dry indefinitely without damage.
Safe for use in hazardous / explosive environments.
Variable flow - simply regulate the inlet air supply to adjust the pump flow from zero to max.
